<item>
            <title>[AMQ-927] Default log4j.properties has stdout enabled and not the out file appender</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-927</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The default log4j.properties has:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;log4j.rootLogger=INFO, stdout
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and then goes on to say:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# CONSOLE appender not used by default
log4j.appender.stdout=org.apache.log4j.ConsoleAppender
..
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And it also has this header... which is misleading:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;#
# The logging properties used during tests..
#
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also not sure why this would be in data... nor do I ever see this being created, even when out is enabled...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;log4j.appender.out.file=${activemq.home}/data/activemq.log
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
